inlineContent.text: domain can come from multiple parts of the protocol stack, many of which define their own error values as part of outside specifications such as the HTTP specification.
To avoid confusion from conflicting error numbers, error codes in the
domain contain two parts: a subdomain, which tells which part of the protocol stack generated the error, and the error code itself.
returns an identifier that tells which layer of the protocol stack produced the error.

returns the actual error code that the subdomain describes. This list of constants contains the possible values that this function will return. They must be interpreted within the context of the relevant error subdomain.
